WEBVTT

00:05.673 --> 00:08.910
[♪♪]

00:11.012 --> 00:12.180
Wow.

00:12.246 --> 00:14.215
Cute place. I guess.

00:16.216 --> 00:18.452
<i>♪ Keep on choogling ♪</i>

00:19.653 --> 00:21.923
<i>♪ Keep on choogling ♪</i>

00:21.990 --> 00:23.557
<i>♪ Keep on choogling ♪</i>

00:23.624 --> 00:25.693
You know, your brother's
my guy for spotting cheats.

00:25.760 --> 00:27.128
And there's nobody better,

00:27.195 --> 00:28.997
but I don't think even he

00:29.063 --> 00:30.431
could spot that. Could you spot that?

00:30.498 --> 00:32.433
One second. What the fuck
is your boss doing here?

00:32.500 --> 00:34.068
- Look, I told him.
- You told him?

00:34.135 --> 00:35.904
- You told him what?
- I think he could help.

00:35.970 --> 00:37.972
Just listen for a second.

00:38.039 --> 00:41.075
I'm sorry.
I... I don't really understand.

00:42.410 --> 00:44.345
What? You need some money?

00:44.412 --> 00:45.814
I'm here, Marius,

00:45.880 --> 00:48.382
because I heard that you
were taking down a cheater.

00:48.449 --> 00:50.451
And I don't like cheaters.

00:50.518 --> 00:51.652
And he's good, Marius.

00:51.719 --> 00:53.287
- You've seen him play?
- No. No.

00:53.354 --> 00:55.089
- But he's been playing for years.
- All right. All right.

00:55.156 --> 00:56.124
He...

00:58.126 --> 00:59.427
You good?

00:59.493 --> 01:00.829
I like to think I am.

01:00.829 --> 01:02.196
Yeah?

01:02.263 --> 01:03.397
Yeah?

01:03.464 --> 01:04.833
Okay.

01:04.866 --> 01:07.301
- That too fast?
- No. Row.

01:07.368 --> 01:09.170
I don't know what my brother told you,

01:09.237 --> 01:11.840
but, we're not looking for card players.

01:11.840 --> 01:13.007
What are you looking for?

01:13.074 --> 01:14.508
What everybody's looking for

01:14.575 --> 01:16.277
deep down in their hearts: money.

01:16.344 --> 01:17.445
What's the buy-in?

01:17.511 --> 01:18.712
Gold Circle's 50.

01:18.847 --> 01:20.081
You get a quarter cut and a T-shirt.

01:20.148 --> 01:22.050
Diamond Circle, you get half the take,

01:22.116 --> 01:23.417
your name in the program.

01:23.484 --> 01:24.685
Fucking program?

01:24.752 --> 01:26.054
Hey, you give me
a hundred thousand dollars

01:26.120 --> 01:27.721
to stake the play,
I'll print the program.

01:27.856 --> 01:29.257
You know, as much as I would love

01:29.323 --> 01:32.360
to have one of your imaginary
T-shirts and programs,

01:32.426 --> 01:34.863
I don't invest in cons.

01:34.863 --> 01:36.865
I've been playing this
game since I was a boy.

01:36.865 --> 01:38.332
My aunt Georgia taught me.

01:38.399 --> 01:43.137
She used to say poker was for boys.

01:43.204 --> 01:45.006
Bridge... [tongue click]...

01:45.073 --> 01:46.908
that's for grownups.

01:49.577 --> 01:50.711
3 of diamonds.

01:50.778 --> 01:52.881
Oh. You're good.

01:54.515 --> 01:56.384
You got that it's a number card in red,

01:56.450 --> 01:57.718
but you're not great.

01:57.785 --> 01:59.320
It's the 6 of hearts.

02:00.955 --> 02:03.791
Sorry you came all this way,
Vince, for nothing.

02:03.892 --> 02:04.993
Try the cherry pie.

02:05.059 --> 02:06.360
- Marius, wait. Wait.
- Eddie... Eddie...

02:06.427 --> 02:08.395
Just give him a second.
Won't you just listen?

02:12.033 --> 02:13.935
- Let me go talk to him.
- Go.

02:15.000 --> 02:21.074
Advertise your product or brand here
