<i>♪ When the going gets rough ♪</i>

08:44.157 --> 08:45.693
<i>♪ And you've had enough ♪</i>

08:45.759 --> 08:47.928
<i>♪ Hit the chicken switch ♪</i>

08:50.298 --> 08:53.534
<i>♪ When the prize ♪</i>

08:53.601 --> 08:56.103
<i>♪ In the game... ♪</i>

08:56.169 --> 08:58.372
Well, not yet, but his people told me

08:58.439 --> 08:59.640
he was looking for a good game,

08:59.707 --> 09:02.476
and I run the best game in town, so...

09:03.844 --> 09:04.778
Uh...

09:05.913 --> 09:07.948
Ah. Don't worry about it.

09:08.015 --> 09:09.717
That's all right. Next time.

09:09.783 --> 09:12.320
No, no, no, no.
There's always a place at my tables

09:12.353 --> 09:13.687
for you, Mr. Mukherjee.

09:13.754 --> 09:15.989
Hmm? Yeah.

09:18.091 --> 09:19.727
He's not coming.

09:19.793 --> 09:21.395
God damn it.

09:21.462 --> 09:22.696
I almost had him

09:22.763 --> 09:25.433
when I told him
Affleck was playing, but...

09:25.499 --> 09:27.568
he's such a starfucker.

09:27.635 --> 09:30.704
So you're rested and rejuvenated?

09:35.008 --> 09:36.644
Yes, I am.

09:36.710 --> 09:37.711
Well...

10:09.777 --> 10:10.978
All right.

10:15.849 --> 10:17.117
I love hockey.

10:17.184 --> 10:20.954
I love Amanda.
I love supporting her dreams.

10:21.021 --> 10:22.490
Yeah. And you love coffee.

10:22.556 --> 10:24.658
Yes, I do. And I love you.

10:25.559 --> 10:26.560
Have a good day.

10:26.627 --> 10:27.695
I'll be home for dinner.

10:27.761 --> 10:29.196
- Yeah?
- All right.

10:29.262 --> 10:31.565
- Who's picking me up?
- I am.

10:31.632 --> 10:33.066
Have a good practice.

10:33.133 --> 10:35.102
All right. Hat trick day.

10:35.168 --> 10:37.405
Ha ha. Go get 'em.

10:37.471 --> 10:38.706
[engine starts]

10:48.482 --> 10:49.717
[door closes]

11:05.165 --> 11:06.434
It's just me.

11:11.171 --> 11:12.973
I said it's just me.

11:13.040 --> 11:15.543
Why do I have the gun?

11:21.949 --> 11:24.452
So Amanda's playing hockey now, huh?

11:24.485 --> 11:26.319
You got to get up at
the crack to get that...

11:26.454 --> 11:27.855
She mentioned you the other day.

11:27.921 --> 11:29.690
Said "Whatever happened to that guy"

11:29.757 --> 11:31.191
"who was around before Brendon?"

11:31.258 --> 11:32.660
Couldn't remember your name.

11:32.726 --> 11:35.496
Maybe because she hasn't
seen you in five years.

11:35.563 --> 11:38.766
Well, you... you told me to leave.

11:39.867 --> 11:41.835
That's how you remember it, huh?

11:41.902 --> 11:44.337
I recall you, uh, dumped me

11:44.472 --> 11:46.339
for someone younger and prettier.

11:46.474 --> 11:47.775
Well, she wasn't prettier,

11:47.841 --> 11:49.477
but she was better at accents.

11:49.543 --> 11:53.146
And then there was her
biggest selling point.

11:53.213 --> 11:55.716
She didn't adopt a kid.

11:57.551 --> 11:58.786
[sigh]

12:00.688 --> 12:03.491
So five years gone. Wow.

12:03.491 --> 12:05.392
In the joint?

12:05.493 --> 12:06.760
Yeah.

12:17.738 --> 12:19.973
I heard about Charlie.

12:20.040 --> 12:22.075
Not the particulars.

12:23.143 --> 12:25.212
[sigh] Anyway, I'm sorry.

12:27.848 --> 12:29.750
I don't have any money, Marius.

12:29.817 --> 12:31.552
Oh, no, no, no, no.
I'm not asking for money.

12:31.619 --> 12:33.386
Then what are you asking for?

12:33.521 --> 12:34.922
Uh, uh, I need you

12:34.988 --> 12:37.290
to backstop me with my parole officer.

12:37.357 --> 12:39.560
I was supposed to check
in a couple of days ago,

12:39.627 --> 12:41.529
and by tomorrow he's going to be on fire.

12:41.562 --> 12:44.097
No. I don't want to have anything to do

12:44.164 --> 12:45.533
with your narrative. No.

12:45.533 --> 12:46.934
You know,
I don't want to have to tell Brendon

12:47.000 --> 12:48.636
- you're running a con.
- I'm not running a con.

12:48.702 --> 12:50.203
Sure you are. Look at you, you know.

12:50.270 --> 12:52.773
You're pretending to be
some suburban housewife,

12:52.840 --> 12:54.608
-  cooking casseroles...
- Thank you.

12:54.675 --> 12:55.976
... and pot roasts and shit.

12:56.043 --> 12:58.078
Okay. Well, according to that definition,

12:58.145 --> 12:59.547
everyone would be running a con.

12:59.613 --> 13:01.148
Fine. Fuck. I'm running a con.

13:01.214 --> 13:02.650
But you know what? This is a con

13:02.716 --> 13:05.252
I plan on running
for the rest of my life.

13:10.724 --> 13:12.325
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to threaten you.

13:12.392 --> 13:13.561
Yeah, you did.

13:13.561 --> 13:15.295
Okay, I'm just desperate.

13:15.362 --> 13:16.864
[sigh]

13:23.003 --> 13:24.905
You should have led with that.

13:31.144 --> 13:33.213
Write down the details of the play.

13:33.280 --> 13:34.982
Keep it simple.

13:41.221 --> 13:43.691
You know anyone driving a black Grand Am?

13:43.757 --> 13:45.392
Force of habit.
I always clock the cars on the block.

13:45.458 --> 13:46.827
I haven't seen that car before.

13:46.894 --> 13:48.996
The place I'm staying,
there's some suspicion.

13:49.062 --> 13:51.999
What? I... I don't want
your shit coming here.

13:52.065 --> 13:53.601
You know, it's really not a big deal.

13:53.667 --> 13:55.202
Hey, I'm going to need a favor.

13:55.268 --> 13:57.437
- Oh, for fuck's sake.
- That thing you did in Wichita.

13:57.504 --> 13:59.039
Do you remember that?

14:01.241 --> 14:03.376
Are you fucking serious?

14:03.443 --> 14:05.312
Please?

14:28.101 --> 14:29.870
Thank you, universe.

14:37.210 --> 14:39.179
[rooster crows]

14:41.081 --> 14:44.752
I wonder what he's been
doing for the last 20 years.

14:50.090 --> 14:52.025
He said insurance.

14:53.460 --> 14:57.097
Well, he wasn't in insurance
when he was a teenager.

14:58.131 --> 15:00.067
We don't know anything about him

15:00.133 --> 15:03.804
except who his father is
and who his mother is.

15:05.072 --> 15:07.675
Who knows how far he fell from that tree?

15:09.309 --> 15:10.410
Look.

15:10.477 --> 15:13.146
I know he snuck out last night.

15:13.213 --> 15:15.783
He hit a squeaky floorboard
and went out the window.

15:15.849 --> 15:17.918
I never heard him come back.

15:19.452 --> 15:20.754
Hey.

15:22.690 --> 15:25.793
The house is still very quiet.

15:30.363 --> 15:33.133
We'll see what the doctor
has to say about that.

15:35.168 --> 15:37.104
I'm not dead yet, for Christ's sakes.

15:38.205 --> 15:40.874
This is going to be a really sad last run

15:40.941 --> 15:42.876
if Dr. Geffen says that's off the table.

15:42.943 --> 15:45.345
It's not all about you, Otto.

15:46.714 --> 15:48.615
How do you think I'd feel if you kick it

15:48.716 --> 15:50.283
when you're on top of me some night?

15:51.518 --> 15:53.921
Nobody says you can't be on top.

16:08.401 --> 16:09.336
Oh.

16:09.402 --> 16:10.537
Hey.

16:10.603 --> 16:11.571
Good morning, Pete.

16:11.638 --> 16:12.873
Good morning.

16:12.940 --> 16:14.374
- How'd you sleep?
- Oh, well, you know,

16:14.441 --> 16:16.944
I'm still getting used
to the bed a little bit.

16:19.847 --> 16:21.749
Eggs will be up in ten.

16:22.850 --> 16:26.153
Actually, to be honest, Grandma,

16:26.219 --> 16:27.220
I, uh...

16:28.756 --> 16:30.257
I didn't sleep at all last night.

16:30.323 --> 16:31.424
Hmm?

16:32.760 --> 16:34.194
I snuck out.

16:34.261 --> 16:36.363
I didn't want to wake you, so I...

16:36.429 --> 16:37.998
I went out the window.

16:39.166 --> 16:42.435
And I... I borrowed your truck.

16:42.502 --> 16:43.937
I went to the city with it.

16:44.004 --> 16:46.974
I drove to White Plains to...
to visit a friend.

16:47.040 --> 16:50.143
Uh, and I am so sorry.

16:50.210 --> 16:51.912
I'll pay you back for the gas.

16:51.979 --> 16:54.447
All you have to do is ask, Pete.

16:54.514 --> 16:56.683
There's no need to sneak around.

16:56.784 --> 16:58.218
I know. I know.

16:58.285 --> 16:59.787
We have an old beater you can use

16:59.853 --> 17:01.154
to get around whenever you need.

17:02.689 --> 17:04.424
Well, thank you.

17:04.491 --> 17:05.657
Hey, I got a question for you.

17:05.792 --> 17:06.659
Yeah?

17:06.794 --> 17:08.228
Whose room am I in?

17:09.596 --> 17:11.064
You don't remember?

17:11.131 --> 17:12.833
I know that it was either
my mother's or my aunt's,

17:12.900 --> 17:14.134
but I can't remember which.

17:14.201 --> 17:17.003
I, uh... I just...
I know that there was a, uh,

17:17.069 --> 17:20.240
an access to an attic
in one of the rooms,

17:20.307 --> 17:22.108
and Taylor and I used to go up there.

17:22.175 --> 17:24.411
We would, uh,
set up our mad scientist lab

17:24.477 --> 17:26.479
and, you know,
mix together potions and all that.

17:26.546 --> 17:27.881
Do you remember that? Yeah.

17:27.948 --> 17:30.050
You made an unholy mess up there.

17:30.117 --> 17:32.019
Well, we were mad scientists.

17:33.020 --> 17:34.855
Uh, the attic access

17:34.922 --> 17:36.723
was in your aunt Lila's room.

17:36.824 --> 17:38.491
This was Maggie's.

17:42.495 --> 17:43.831
You changed it.

17:45.598 --> 17:46.934
Yes, I did.

18:08.221 --> 18:10.123
[mouthing]

18:15.728 --> 18:17.364
Julia: You look tired.

18:18.565 --> 18:19.867
Studying for the exam.

18:19.933 --> 18:21.401
Oh, yeah? How's that going?

18:21.468 --> 18:22.569
It's going.

18:22.635 --> 18:24.371
Did you know in the state of Connecticut,

18:24.437 --> 18:27.274
for a pickle to be considered a pickle,

18:27.340 --> 18:28.909
it must bounce?

18:28.976 --> 18:31.378
You studying to become a food inspector?

18:31.444 --> 18:34.414
Taylor's going to take
his detective exam... again.

18:34.481 --> 18:36.783
Well, at least he's
trying to accomplish something.

18:36.884 --> 18:38.551
She was just joking, Audrey.

18:38.618 --> 18:39.752
I was?

18:39.887 --> 18:41.889
So when are we going to head to Pine Top?

18:41.889 --> 18:44.091
- Hmm?
- Uh, yeah.

18:44.157 --> 18:46.793
Whenever you...
Whenever you want to do that.

18:46.894 --> 18:48.461
You...

18:48.528 --> 18:51.198
You remember when we...
we blew up that old truck?

18:51.264 --> 18:55.102
Right?
With all that... that stolen dynamite?

18:55.168 --> 18:56.603
Hmm?

18:56.669 --> 18:58.005
Do you remember that?

18:58.071 --> 19:01.441
My sainted brother broke the law?

19:01.508 --> 19:03.310
No, I... It was...

19:03.376 --> 19:06.146
We blew up a paint
can with a firecracker.

19:06.213 --> 19:08.715
Oh, Grandpa,
I was hoping to leave Jacob with you

19:08.781 --> 19:10.383
while I went to the shop today.

19:10.450 --> 19:12.485
I knew you'd forget. I told you

19:12.552 --> 19:14.387
I have to take Otto to
the doctor this morning.

19:14.454 --> 19:16.223
When are you going to
line up some day care

19:16.289 --> 19:18.191
- that isn't your grandfather?
- I don't mind.

19:19.392 --> 19:20.827
I don't mind.

19:20.928 --> 19:22.362
We'll come over to the shop right after.

19:22.429 --> 19:23.630
Hey, you know, I can go with Julia

19:23.696 --> 19:25.032
and watch Jacob.

19:25.098 --> 19:26.699
You know, I got to learn the job.

19:26.766 --> 19:28.435
You ever babysat a 2-year-old?

19:28.501 --> 19:31.071
Yeah, I find that with their first beer,
they're really easy.

19:46.954 --> 19:49.089
[phone rings]

19:49.156 --> 19:50.557
[singing on radio]

19:50.623 --> 19:52.825
Hey. What do you have?

19:52.960 --> 19:57.097
Uh, left your place around 10.

19:57.164 --> 19:59.399
Drove to the city. Parked in Chinatown.

19:59.466 --> 20:01.901
A woman came out... beautiful, money.

20:01.969 --> 20:04.271
Stays there, mm, an hour

20:04.337 --> 20:05.738
and then drives to a house

20:05.805 --> 20:07.107
in White Plains.

20:07.174 --> 20:09.076
Stayed there till about 1.

20:09.142 --> 20:11.478
Slept in the truck a few hours.

20:11.544 --> 20:12.712
At least I assume he...

20:12.779 --> 20:14.047
he slept. I know I did.

20:14.114 --> 20:15.915
Uh, a little before dawn,

20:15.983 --> 20:18.751
he goes into a house,

20:18.818 --> 20:20.720
into a house,

20:20.787 --> 20:24.591
meets with a woman for a bed.

20:24.657 --> 20:26.326
Heads back to the party.

20:26.393 --> 20:28.028
He clocked you?

20:28.095 --> 20:29.796
Probably. I'm terrible at this.

20:29.862 --> 20:32.132
He told me he skipped out,
took my truck into the city.

20:32.199 --> 20:34.734
I wondered if maybe he
knew he'd been followed,

20:34.801 --> 20:37.237
was trying to play off my suspicions.

20:37.304 --> 20:38.471
Whatever you're thinking

20:38.538 --> 20:40.573
your long-lost grandson is up to,

20:40.640 --> 20:42.542
he is in a situation.

20:42.609 --> 20:43.643
What kind?

20:43.710 --> 20:45.545
The oldes... well, the second oldest.

20:45.612 --> 20:48.648
The woman in White Plains is Katie Boyd.

20:48.715 --> 20:52.052
Husband is Brendon Boyd.

20:52.119 --> 20:55.055
Pretty sure your Pete is bumping uglies

20:55.122 --> 20:56.456
with Mrs. Katie Boyd.

20:56.523 --> 20:59.492
You want me to stay on him?

21:01.228 --> 21:04.131
Uh, maybe I just
picked up on the cheating.

21:04.197 --> 21:06.299
- Set off my alarms.
- Yeah, you do have

21:06.366 --> 21:07.934
a pretty good instinct in that regard.

21:08.035 --> 21:11.671
How much longer do I have
to keep doing shit for you?

21:11.738 --> 21:13.573
I mean, I'm not asking for
the exact date,

21:13.640 --> 21:16.076
- more general.
- Oh, I don't know, Sam.

21:16.143 --> 21:17.877
I'd say you have to keep
doing what I ask you

21:17.944 --> 21:20.180
until you pay what you owe.

21:32.625 --> 21:34.594
I thought you were getting ready.

21:35.862 --> 21:37.264
I'm ready.

21:41.234 --> 21:42.635
<i>Julia: Miss Trotosian,</i>

21:42.702 --> 21:44.537
<i>I've talked to his lawyer and the jail.</i>

21:44.604 --> 21:48.108
<i>Bring all the documentation
and the check,</i>

21:48.175 --> 21:50.210
<i>and we should have him out after lunch.</i>

21:53.913 --> 21:55.148
Nice.

21:56.083 --> 21:57.150
Well,

21:57.217 --> 21:58.585
my whale thinks he's a big shot,

21:58.651 --> 22:00.320
so we got to treat him like a big shot,
right?

22:00.387 --> 22:02.089
I don't make up the rules.

22:02.155 --> 22:03.323
Who's the whale?

22:03.390 --> 22:05.125
His name is, uh, Charles McGregor.

22:05.192 --> 22:06.993
He, runs... well, he ran

22:07.094 --> 22:08.628
a small, very successful hedge fund,

22:08.695 --> 22:10.797
and now he, uh, plays bridge full time.

22:10.863 --> 22:13.566
Uh, another Wall Street
asshole playing bridge, huh?

22:13.633 --> 22:14.701
[chuckling]

22:14.767 --> 22:16.769
So what's the play?

22:16.836 --> 22:19.606
We draw him and his partner
into a high-stakes game.

22:19.672 --> 22:22.242
We let them win for three weeks in a row,

22:22.309 --> 22:23.643
and then we clean him out.

22:26.113 --> 22:27.380
How does he cheat?

22:27.447 --> 22:29.116
What is it, a cough code,

22:29.182 --> 22:32.485
or are we playing footsies
like the Italians?

22:32.552 --> 22:34.587
Uh, yeah,
it took me a while to figure it out.

22:34.654 --> 22:37.124
At first I thought it was
like the Norwegians, right?

22:37.190 --> 22:40.260
But then I noticed how he moves
his cards when he's sorting.

22:40.327 --> 22:43.830
The first card he moves
indicates the suit.

22:43.896 --> 22:46.333
If he moves it all the way to the left,
it's spades.

22:46.399 --> 22:48.268
Second slot is hearts, so on, so forth.

22:48.335 --> 22:50.237
Second card indicates a number,

22:50.303 --> 22:51.738
which he moves to the right.

22:51.804 --> 22:53.640
Ah, very good.

22:53.706 --> 22:56.276
Good eye. Okay. Saying you're right...

22:56.343 --> 22:57.877
- I am right.
- Which, well, we'll see.

22:57.944 --> 22:59.279
I'm right.

22:59.346 --> 23:00.580
I still don't see the play.

23:00.647 --> 23:02.415
I mean, how do we cheat the cheater?

23:02.482 --> 23:04.184
We can't leave it to chance.

23:04.251 --> 23:05.618
No, no, no, no. No.

23:05.685 --> 23:07.420
I never leave anything to chance.

23:07.487 --> 23:10.022
No, I got... I got an inside man.

23:10.157 --> 23:13.193
Not a man but a woman.

23:17.564 --> 23:18.231
That's you.

23:18.298 --> 23:20.867
Yes, it's me.

23:24.671 --> 23:26.673
Thank you for choosing
Bernhardt Bail Bonds.

23:26.739 --> 23:28.575
We know you have a choice
when it comes...

23:28.641 --> 23:29.842
[click, dial tone]

23:33.246 --> 23:35.848
Whoo-hoo. Another $200.

23:35.915 --> 23:37.384
We're saved.

23:38.585 --> 23:39.519
I got a question

23:39.586 --> 23:41.321
I've wanted answered for 20 years.

23:41.388 --> 23:43.856
What's in the safe?

23:46.493 --> 23:48.628
No, I just... I just have a memory

23:48.695 --> 23:50.062
of all of us wondering what was in there.

23:50.197 --> 23:51.798
Oh, just say it.

23:51.864 --> 23:52.799
What?

23:52.865 --> 23:54.033
"Rublies."

23:54.100 --> 23:55.101
What?

23:55.202 --> 23:56.336
You don't remember rublies?

23:56.403 --> 23:58.638
When we were kids,

23:58.705 --> 24:02.409
I said there might be gold
and diamonds and rublies.

24:02.475 --> 24:04.344
- Oh, right.
- I thought there was an L in it.

24:04.411 --> 24:05.645
That was hilarious.

24:05.712 --> 24:06.479
Yeah, for you.

24:06.546 --> 24:07.914
Called me rublies for a week.

24:07.980 --> 24:10.417
I was just happy you
were calling me anything.

24:10.483 --> 24:11.451
So...

24:12.719 --> 24:13.820
Yeah, well,

24:13.886 --> 24:15.688
so there's no gold and rublies in there,
huh?

24:15.755 --> 24:17.123
[snickering]

24:17.224 --> 24:19.226
Life was better when we were 10.

24:20.393 --> 24:22.061
Yeah, it's mostly collateral.

24:22.128 --> 24:23.996
Some jewelry, silverware,

24:24.063 --> 24:26.666
a rare book once. Why?
You thinking of robbing it?

24:26.733 --> 24:28.768
Well, not if that's all that's in there.

24:30.069 --> 24:31.371
- Hey.
- Hey.

24:31.438 --> 24:33.273
Uh, I got a couple of people

24:33.340 --> 24:35.275
coming by later to fill out paperwork

24:35.342 --> 24:36.776
and drop off a check.

24:36.843 --> 24:38.245
Thought I'd take Pete
with me out on rounds.

24:38.311 --> 24:40.112
Jacob's down for his nap.

24:40.247 --> 24:42.582
Snacks and juice are in the bag.

24:42.649 --> 24:43.816
And, uh, thanks.

24:43.883 --> 24:45.252
Our pleasure, sweetheart.

24:45.285 --> 24:46.719
How was the, uh, the doctor, Grandpa?

24:46.786 --> 24:47.887
Oh, he said I was fine.

24:47.954 --> 24:49.622
He said you shouldn't exert yourself.

24:49.689 --> 24:52.259
He said I shouldn't exert myself

24:52.292 --> 24:53.826
any more than any man my age.

24:53.893 --> 24:55.094
And how old are you?

24:55.161 --> 24:57.163
25 when I look in the mirror.

24:57.264 --> 24:59.299
<i>♪ Surprise ♪</i>

24:59.366 --> 25:00.733
<i>♪ Let go ♪</i>

25:00.800 --> 25:03.035
You didn't tell Grandma about Persikof,
did you?

25:03.102 --> 25:05.472
Oh, I will. Soon.

25:06.673 --> 25:07.340
Some day.

25:07.407 --> 25:09.509
Maybe on her deathbed.

25:09.576 --> 25:10.410
Or mine.

25:10.477 --> 25:11.544
The way things are right now,

25:11.611 --> 25:12.679
I'll probably check out first.

25:12.745 --> 25:14.414
What happens now with Persikof?

25:14.481 --> 25:15.948
Well, Connecticut and
New York fight over him.

25:16.015 --> 25:17.950
New York probably wins,
murder trumping tax evasion.

25:18.017 --> 25:20.052
Right, but New York doesn't
know Connecticut has him, right?

25:20.119 --> 25:21.921
You didn't tell Taylor
about the New York warrant,

25:21.988 --> 25:24.023
and I'm pretty sure Persikof
didn't say anything.

25:24.090 --> 25:25.525
What are you thinking?
You're thinking something.

25:25.592 --> 25:27.159
Does Persikof get another bail hearing?

25:27.294 --> 25:28.395
This morning, but it'll be short.

25:28.461 --> 25:29.996
Bail will be revoked because he skipped.

25:30.062 --> 25:31.298
Okay, so this is...

25:31.331 --> 25:32.765
this is where it gets
a little complicated

25:32.832 --> 25:35.635
because I... I quit my
insurance job so abruptly,

25:35.702 --> 25:39.306
my former boss is being
slow on my last paycheck,

25:39.339 --> 25:41.374
and, because I was living
hand to mouth...

25:41.441 --> 25:43.209
You want money? We're broke.

25:43.310 --> 25:44.477
No, no, no. I'm just saying.

25:44.544 --> 25:46.446
If new... new bail is granted,

25:46.513 --> 25:49.882
then, you know, maybe...
maybe I... I... I get half.

25:49.949 --> 25:52.385
New bail?
This guy's beyond a flight risk.

25:52.452 --> 25:54.387
But this time is collateral,

25:54.454 --> 25:57.690
you get, you know,
uh, his mother's house.

25:58.725 --> 26:01.461
I could give you 10%, tops.

26:01.528 --> 26:02.729
But it better be a brilliant plan.

26:02.795 --> 26:04.130
- It's a real...
- Let's hear it.

26:04.196 --> 26:05.765
Okay. So we go to Persikof's lawyer...

26:05.832 --> 26:07.334
Mm-mm.

26:07.400 --> 26:09.936
What, you know him?

26:10.002 --> 26:13.105
I do. Long story.

26:13.172 --> 26:15.207
Can you get past it?

26:15.342 --> 26:16.709
I can try.

26:16.776 --> 26:18.711
And now it's got to be
the best plan ever.

26:18.778 --> 26:21.648
It starts with a simple question.

26:21.714 --> 26:24.517
What if Persikof didn't skip?

26:25.385 --> 26:26.419
But he did skip.

26:26.486 --> 26:27.820
Humor me for one second.

26:27.887 --> 26:30.022
How much additional bail would be set?

26:30.089 --> 26:32.559
I don't know. Uh, 100,000, 150.

26:32.625 --> 26:35.695
Which means you would get
another $10 to $15,000, right?

26:39.799 --> 26:41.368
When the judge asks why you skipped,

26:41.401 --> 26:42.702
what do you say?

26:42.769 --> 26:44.871
I didn't skip. I got the dates wrong.

26:44.937 --> 26:46.706
What did the police report say?

26:46.773 --> 26:50.377
Whatever that awful bail
woman said is a lie.

26:50.443 --> 26:51.944
Uh, well, you know,

26:52.011 --> 26:54.681
the police report didn't say much. Why?

26:54.747 --> 26:56.282
- Nothing about New York?
- Ma.

26:56.383 --> 26:57.784
[beeping]

26:57.850 --> 27:00.553
Is there something I should know about?

27:00.620 --> 27:01.588
No.

27:05.992 --> 27:07.059
Excuse me.

27:15.267 --> 27:17.770
I'm guessing you're mad at me.

27:17.837 --> 27:19.739
Why would I be mad at you, Lance?

27:19.806 --> 27:21.408
I was just trying to help you out.

27:21.474 --> 27:22.709
A client with bogus collateral.

27:22.775 --> 27:24.243
Okay, now, I didn't know that.

27:24.310 --> 27:25.445
Wanted for murder in New York.

27:25.512 --> 27:26.713
- What?
- You gonna pretend

27:26.779 --> 27:28.180
you didn't know about that?

27:28.247 --> 27:29.916
You honestly think I
would send you a murderer?

27:29.982 --> 27:31.884
Nothing you could do would surprise me.

27:31.951 --> 27:33.252
Is that why we're here?

27:33.319 --> 27:34.754
That's not why we're here, right?

27:34.821 --> 27:36.222
- Who's he?
- Hi. I'm Pete.

27:36.288 --> 27:37.256
Pete Murphy.

27:37.323 --> 27:39.191
Who is Pete Murphy?

27:39.258 --> 27:40.927
My long-lost cousin.

27:43.129 --> 27:44.531
Yeah, okay.

27:44.597 --> 27:46.433
If you have anything more
to accuse me of,

27:46.433 --> 27:47.700
can you make it quick?

27:47.767 --> 27:49.436
My client's bail hearing
is about to start.

27:49.436 --> 27:51.203
We know, and before
it does, we'd like you

27:51.270 --> 27:52.572
to ask your client a question

27:52.639 --> 27:54.206
about what happened the other night.

27:54.273 --> 27:56.643
See, I got hit in the head,

27:56.709 --> 27:58.645
and my mem...
my memory's all scrambled up.

27:58.711 --> 28:01.614
I can't remember if we were
running your client to ground

28:01.681 --> 28:03.315
because he was trying to skip

28:03.450 --> 28:06.318
or if it was all just
an innocent mistake.

28:06.453 --> 28:07.554
I can't remember

28:07.620 --> 28:09.321
if your client took my cousin's gun

28:09.456 --> 28:10.723
and his mother suggest that he shoot her

28:10.790 --> 28:12.459
or if it was all very amicable,

28:12.492 --> 28:15.995
ending in me unfortunately but innocently

28:16.062 --> 28:17.764
suffering a blow to my face.

28:17.830 --> 28:20.299
So if you could just ask your client

28:20.366 --> 28:21.801
which version is correct.

28:21.868 --> 28:23.603
Honestly, I just want my memory back

28:23.670 --> 28:24.904
because, in the end,

28:24.971 --> 28:26.506
is there anything more
important than memories?

28:26.573 --> 28:28.741
Yes, there are more important things,

28:28.808 --> 28:30.009
like not getting disbarred.

28:30.076 --> 28:31.644
Oh, Lance, you know, if you don't feel

28:31.711 --> 28:32.879
like you can sell it...

28:32.945 --> 28:33.980
Oh, Cousin Pete,

28:34.046 --> 28:35.848
you really think goading
me is going to work?

28:35.915 --> 28:38.518
- No. I'm not...
- Hey, hey, hey, hey.

28:38.585 --> 28:39.919
You owe me.

28:41.488 --> 28:42.822
<i>Bailiff: All rise.</i>

28:47.093 --> 28:48.360
Practice your signals.

28:48.495 --> 28:50.062
- [laughing]
- Yes, sir.

28:52.499 --> 28:53.700
- Hey.
- What?

28:53.766 --> 28:55.735
- Going on a break.
- Yeah, yeah. Good idea.

28:55.802 --> 28:57.504
I'm gonna grab a Sixer
and watch the game.

28:57.570 --> 28:59.706
- You want to come?
- Ah, no. I'm gonna...

28:59.772 --> 29:00.940
Sit here and worry?

29:01.007 --> 29:02.942
Yeah. Well, one of us has to, you...

29:03.009 --> 29:04.010
All right.

29:05.344 --> 29:07.179
Hey, go easy tonight.

29:07.246 --> 29:08.247
Yeah.

29:08.314 --> 29:09.516
Yeah.

29:13.520 --> 29:15.387
<i>- Vince: So, Karolina.</i>
- Huh.

29:15.522 --> 29:17.323
- Where do you live?
- Downtown.

29:17.389 --> 29:19.526
Oh, yeah? Can I give you a ride?

29:20.960 --> 29:22.829
That... That is most appreciated.

29:22.895 --> 29:25.064
Sure. Here.
It's a little chilly out there.

29:25.131 --> 29:26.733
Let me help you with it.

29:27.734 --> 29:29.802
You know, that accent of yours.

29:32.739 --> 29:34.073
When I was a kid,

29:34.140 --> 29:35.575
I had this mad crush

29:35.642 --> 29:37.577
on Natasha from "Bullwinkle."

29:37.644 --> 29:40.613
- [whistle]
- What is, uh, Bullwinkle?

29:41.548 --> 29:42.882
What is Bullwinkle?

29:42.949 --> 29:44.584
You didn't have Rocky and Bullwinkle...

29:44.651 --> 29:45.852
- No.
- ... the cartoon in Slo...

29:45.918 --> 29:47.153
- Slovenia.
- Slovenia.

29:47.219 --> 29:48.220
Slovenia.

29:48.287 --> 29:49.556
Slovenia.

29:49.556 --> 29:50.723
You see, when I say it,

29:50.790 --> 29:52.559
it sounds like
the armpit of the universe,

29:52.625 --> 29:54.460
but not when you say it.

29:54.561 --> 29:56.596
It just sounds like Utopia.

29:56.663 --> 29:58.164
- Stop it.
- No, I'm not kidding you.

29:58.230 --> 29:59.198
You're too much.

29:59.265 --> 30:00.332
I'm too much?

30:00.399 --> 30:01.500
But do tell me,

30:01.568 --> 30:03.035
what is this Bullwinkle?

30:03.102 --> 30:04.971
Bullwinkle was a moose.

30:13.613 --> 30:15.414
Hey, pal, you got the time?

30:15.481 --> 30:16.949
Yeah.

30:17.016 --> 30:18.084
Fuck!

30:21.287 --> 30:22.354
Hello, Eddie.

30:22.421 --> 30:25.257
My name is Detective Frank Winslow.

30:25.324 --> 30:26.559
I know the con

30:26.626 --> 30:28.194
you and your brother are running.

30:28.260 --> 30:30.663
I also know you don't tell the truth.

30:30.730 --> 30:32.331
The next time you get this close

30:32.398 --> 30:33.866
to an alcoholic beverage,

30:33.933 --> 30:35.902
it'll be when your cellie shares the wine

30:35.968 --> 30:37.904
he just made in the toilet.

30:44.844 --> 30:47.980
We just made $20,000!

30:48.047 --> 30:49.949
[laughing]

30:50.016 --> 30:53.285
Oh, I can't believe
Judge Banks bought it.

30:53.352 --> 30:54.553
Yeah.

30:54.621 --> 30:56.288
I got a question.

30:56.355 --> 30:57.423
Yeah.

30:57.489 --> 30:58.925
If the company's so strapped,

30:58.991 --> 31:00.492
how do you guys post bail?

31:00.559 --> 31:02.128
That's where the line of credit comes in.

31:02.194 --> 31:03.129
Oh. Right. Yeah.

31:03.195 --> 31:05.632
Okay, so what now? You take the money?

31:05.632 --> 31:07.399
You put it in the safe with the rublies?

31:07.466 --> 31:08.935
No. After they finish the paperwork,

31:09.001 --> 31:11.037
I get a check and deposit it in the bank.

31:12.739 --> 31:14.206
Okay, so for my cut...

31:14.273 --> 31:15.474
And then you get your cut.

31:15.541 --> 31:16.508
Worth every penny.

31:16.643 --> 31:18.310
Very smart play, Cousin Pete.

31:18.377 --> 31:20.412
But I was wondering if
I could get that in cash

31:20.479 --> 31:21.814
- if possible.
- Uh...

31:21.881 --> 31:23.349
What?

31:23.415 --> 31:26.518
The Persikofs have decided
to bond out with A&B.

31:26.653 --> 31:29.421
A&B? They... They... They can't do that.

31:29.488 --> 31:30.522
We... We had a deal.

31:30.657 --> 31:32.558
We had a deal, you and me.

31:32.659 --> 31:34.560
But they just fired me as their attorney.

31:34.661 --> 31:36.696
I'm sorry, Julia.

31:36.763 --> 31:40.499
Lance, you better run now

31:40.566 --> 31:41.934
