- You sure?
- Yes.

47:14.600 --> 47:16.902
Yes, yes.

47:16.968 --> 47:19.070
We'd better do the nose.

47:19.137 --> 47:20.071
What?

47:20.138 --> 47:21.072
Ah, come on.

47:21.139 --> 47:22.908
Oh, fuck.

47:22.974 --> 47:24.810
All right, hang on, hang on.

47:24.876 --> 47:27.512
You know what?
Something's really bugging me here.

47:27.613 --> 47:30.782
I thought things between
you and me were good.

47:31.850 --> 47:33.652
I mean, you earned my trust

47:33.719 --> 47:35.320
the past few years.

47:35.386 --> 47:36.988
I gave you your freedom.

47:37.055 --> 47:38.624
And what? Now you're just... pew!

47:38.624 --> 47:40.692
- You take off?
- If I was so freedom,

47:40.759 --> 47:42.861
then why did Richard
sic Hush Puppy on me?

47:42.928 --> 47:46.865
Well, there's free
and then there's free.

47:46.932 --> 47:50.101
No. Something happened, Eddie.

47:50.168 --> 47:52.437
Why run now?

47:52.503 --> 47:54.239
Hmm?

47:55.540 --> 47:56.942
Someone got to you, didn't they?

47:58.777 --> 48:00.278
It was Marius, wasn't it?

48:00.345 --> 48:02.047
He got through to you, huh?

48:02.113 --> 48:04.716
Sent you a warning or a little message

48:04.783 --> 48:07.318
or some code or something like that?

48:07.385 --> 48:09.220
Huh? How did it go down, Eddie?

48:09.287 --> 48:10.689
How'd he do it?

48:13.458 --> 48:15.994
<i>Richard: My phone.</i>

48:16.061 --> 48:16.928
What?

48:16.995 --> 48:18.864
Rang three times in a row.

48:18.930 --> 48:21.366
A number I didn't recognize.

48:23.902 --> 48:24.936
Oops.

48:28.006 --> 48:29.741
Okay. Now we're getting somewhere.

48:29.808 --> 48:31.376
So we know Eddie was warned...

48:31.442 --> 48:33.879
by Marius, undoubtedly.

48:35.413 --> 48:37.348
But...

48:37.415 --> 48:39.017
how did Marius know

48:39.084 --> 48:41.352
that Richie was watching Eddie?

48:43.021 --> 48:45.023
He knows Richard's your best guy.

48:45.090 --> 48:46.925
And he thought you'd put him on Eddie.

48:48.694 --> 48:50.929
What I want to know is how
the hell did he get my number.

48:50.996 --> 48:53.131
I don't give out my number.

48:56.534 --> 48:57.502
Marius.

48:57.568 --> 48:59.705
Come on, Marius.

49:01.172 --> 49:03.008
- Pass code?
- First two numbers

49:03.074 --> 49:05.143
are double upper left...
either two 1s or two 4s.

49:08.714 --> 49:10.348
When Marius does a con,

49:10.415 --> 49:11.717
he gets every number he can.

49:11.783 --> 49:13.719
He figured it out from that stinking

49:13.752 --> 49:15.520
Jim Brown jersey you never take off.

49:15.586 --> 49:18.156
Jim Brown was number 32 in Cleveland

49:18.223 --> 49:20.892
and 44 at Syracuse.

49:20.959 --> 49:23.194
Syracuse and Cleveland it was.

49:23.261 --> 49:25.330
You know he was also a
great lacrosse player?

49:25.396 --> 49:26.732
That's a nice lift.

49:26.765 --> 49:29.034
Yeah. I'll say.

49:29.100 --> 49:32.570
Of course, boy,
that memory of his is impressive.

49:32.637 --> 49:34.405
Really, and that was three years ago.

49:34.472 --> 49:36.541
- Memory palaces.
- Huh?

49:36.607 --> 49:40.645
He builds what he calls
memory palaces in his head.

49:40.746 --> 49:42.247
Memory palaces?

49:43.414 --> 49:44.950
What the fuck is that?

49:45.016 --> 49:47.318
Sounds, uh, fancy.

49:49.387 --> 49:50.621
All right.

49:50.756 --> 49:52.858
What do we know?

49:52.924 --> 49:56.594
We'll, uh, we'll trace the phone.

49:56.661 --> 49:58.429
See if we can get a location back.

49:58.496 --> 49:59.564
But, Marius being Marius,

49:59.630 --> 50:00.766
he probably thought of that,

50:00.766 --> 50:02.067
so...

50:02.133 --> 50:04.169
I guess it's still worth a try.

50:04.235 --> 50:06.137
You've been very helpful, Eddie.

50:06.204 --> 50:07.138
Thank you.

50:10.508 --> 50:11.642
Do the nose.

50:11.709 --> 50:12.978
Oh, fuck.

50:22.653 --> 50:23.688
Thank you.

50:23.755 --> 50:25.223
You earned it.

50:27.158 --> 50:31.496
Hey, uh, I'm sorry about not
sticking up for you earlier

50:31.562 --> 50:33.664
with Audrey.

50:33.731 --> 50:34.800
No problem.

50:34.866 --> 50:35.967
I'm still... I'm still

50:36.034 --> 50:37.769
just sort of catching up on things.

50:39.871 --> 50:42.774
Was she always that mean
to you when we were kids?

50:43.775 --> 50:44.910
No.

50:46.444 --> 50:48.279
I used to get angry and fight with her,

50:48.346 --> 50:51.349
but nothing changed, so why even try?

50:53.952 --> 50:55.420
You still glad you came back?

50:58.589 --> 51:00.225
Uh, yeah. Yeah.

51:05.630 --> 51:09.200
Pete, your memories of this place...

51:09.267 --> 51:12.037
it hasn't been like that since...

51:13.138 --> 51:15.306
well, since you and your mom left.

51:17.042 --> 51:18.676
I don't know what you expected to find,

51:18.743 --> 51:20.045
but it's not here anymore.

51:20.111 --> 51:21.880
I mean, I'm a single mom

51:21.947 --> 51:24.515
with two kids by two different dads,

51:24.582 --> 51:27.418
making about $1.98 an hour

51:27.485 --> 51:30.155
working for a grandmother
who treats me like shit.

51:30.221 --> 51:34.492
Your cousin Taylor is a man-child

51:34.559 --> 51:35.861
who says he wants to grow up

51:35.894 --> 51:37.863
but still acts like a 16-year-old.

51:37.863 --> 51:40.065
And then you have an
actual 16-year-old cousin

51:40.131 --> 51:41.900
who thinks Taylor's
the only one who knows

51:41.967 --> 51:44.569
she's been pinched a couple
times for shoplifting.

51:44.635 --> 51:48.106
Add to that the family
business is circling the drain.

51:48.173 --> 51:49.440
And...

51:51.109 --> 51:52.777
if I'd known you were coming,

51:52.878 --> 51:55.013
I would have told you
to run for the hills.

52:07.325 --> 52:08.559
[knocking]

52:08.626 --> 52:10.461
[engine starts]

52:22.140 --> 52:24.375
Because this family is fucking crazy.

52:24.442 --> 52:28.013
Uh, you can handle crazy for a few days.

52:28.079 --> 52:29.314
All right? What about the safe?

52:29.380 --> 52:30.982
They just keep collateral in there...

52:31.049 --> 52:32.417
jewelry and silver.

52:32.483 --> 52:34.185
There's nothing even
close to what I need.

52:34.252 --> 52:36.154
You have six days until Vince removes

52:36.221 --> 52:37.522
one of Eddie's fingers.

52:37.588 --> 52:39.925
I... I know that.
All right? I know that.

52:39.958 --> 52:41.126
That is not a lot of time

52:41.192 --> 52:43.094
to go somewhere and start from scratch.

52:43.161 --> 52:44.930
I was thinking Atlantic City.

52:44.996 --> 52:46.831
There's got to be
new people in the casinos

52:46.932 --> 52:48.599
that don't know me, right?

52:48.666 --> 52:50.701
I saw Karolina.

52:50.768 --> 52:52.370
Well? How did she seem?

52:52.437 --> 52:54.239
She seems scared.

52:54.305 --> 52:56.541
She still doesn't want to talk to you.

52:57.842 --> 52:59.577
<i>We might not get her, Marius.</i>

52:59.644 --> 53:03.381
I know how much you want
to pull off the Turk,

53:03.448 --> 53:04.983
<i>but, um,</i>

53:05.050 --> 53:06.617
I don't think we can do it without her.

53:14.825 --> 53:17.228
- Hey.
- Oh, my God.

53:18.296 --> 53:19.764
You scared the shit out of me.

53:19.830 --> 53:20.966
What are you doing?

53:20.999 --> 53:23.301
You're really leaving this time.

53:23.368 --> 53:24.435
Aren't you?

53:26.537 --> 53:27.472
What?

53:28.639 --> 53:29.607
Uh, I'm not leaving.

53:29.674 --> 53:30.641
What do you mean?

53:30.708 --> 53:32.277
Don't lie to me.

53:33.711 --> 53:35.713
I can't stand all the lying.

53:35.780 --> 53:37.248
You, uh...

53:38.483 --> 53:39.784
Hey, don't worry.

53:39.850 --> 53:42.320
They've been asleep for, like, an hour.

53:48.426 --> 53:49.294
Uh, I don't...

53:49.360 --> 53:50.861
- It's mellow.
- I'm not...

53:50.996 --> 53:52.030
No paranoia.

53:52.097 --> 53:53.564
Okay. Yeah. Give it to me.

53:57.902 --> 53:58.869
Can I come with you?

53:59.004 --> 54:00.071
Mm.

54:01.439 --> 54:02.373
I'm just...

54:03.608 --> 54:05.110
[coughing]

54:05.176 --> 54:06.811
I'm just going into the city.

54:06.877 --> 54:08.679
I'm just going into the city tonight.

54:10.615 --> 54:11.782
A few months back,

54:11.849 --> 54:14.085
if I'd had the combo to that safe,

54:14.152 --> 54:17.055
I'd already be long over the horizon.

54:18.023 --> 54:19.290
I say that, but...

54:20.425 --> 54:22.493
Grandma and Grandpa
have one dead daughter

54:22.560 --> 54:26.131
and... another that's dead to them.

54:27.032 --> 54:28.266
No offense.

54:29.134 --> 54:30.535
Me running with their money

54:30.601 --> 54:31.702
wouldn't kill them.

54:33.204 --> 54:34.939
Well, you probably wouldn't get too far

54:35.040 --> 54:37.275
with jewelry and silverware, right?

54:37.342 --> 54:39.144
- The collateral?
- Yeah.

54:39.210 --> 54:41.112
That's nothing.
I'm talking about the cash box.

54:41.179 --> 54:43.048
- The what?
- They still think I'm 6

54:43.114 --> 54:45.050
and don't know
what they're talking about,

54:45.050 --> 54:48.353
but they bonded a guy out a while back,

54:48.419 --> 54:52.223
and he put down the entire
bail amount in cash.

54:52.290 --> 54:58.263
Right now there's, like, $150,000

54:58.329 --> 55:00.231
sitting in that safe.

55:03.601 --> 55:04.735
[laughing]

